r-tab-content-2582\" class=\"elementor-tab-content elementor-clearfix\" data-tab=\"2\" role=\"tabpanel\" aria-labelledby=\"elementor-tab-title-2582\" tabindex=\"0\" hidden=\"hidden\"><p style=\"margin: 0cm;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"color: #0e101a;\">Brown-Banded Cockroaches measure around 1\/2 to 5\/8 inches in length.<\/span><\/p><\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-tab-title elementor-tab-mobile-title\" aria-selected=\"false\" data-tab=\"3\" role=\"tab\" tabindex=\"-1\" aria-controls=\"elementor-tab-content-2583\" aria-expanded=\"false\">Description<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t<div id=\"elementor-tab-content-2583\" class=\"elementor-tab-content elementor-clearfix\" data-tab=\"3\" role=\"tabpanel\" aria-labelledby=\"elementor-tab-title-2583\" tabindex=\"0\" hidden=\"hidden\"><p style=\"margin: 0cm;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"color: #0e101a;\">Brown-Banded Cockroach&#8217;s body structure consists of the head, thorax, and abdomen. The head contains sensory organs such as compound eyes, antennae, and mouthparts. The thorax comprises the six legs, which are used for mobility. The brown-banded cockroach&#8217;s body is covered with a hard exoskeleton that offers protection against predators or environmental factors.<\/span><\/p><\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-column elementor-col-33 elementor-top-column elementor-element elementor-element-5219e3c\" data-id=\"5219e3c\" data-element_type=\"column\">\n\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-wrap\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-column elementor-col-33 elementor-top-column elementor-element elementor-element-449115c\" data-id=\"449115c\" data-element_type=\"column\" data-settings=\"{&quot;background_background&quot;:&quot;classic&quot;}\">\n\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-wrap elementor-element-populated\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-elem